The Lagos State government has said that the enforcement and review of safety regulations, equipment, machinery and manufacturing places will continue unabated because the safety and health of all residents are of paramount interest to the present administration. The Director-General, Lagos State Safety Commission, Lanre Mojola, said this on Thursday, during a one-day training on safe workplaces, equipment, machinery and practice in manufacturing companies in Alausa, Ikeja. The workshop was organised by Lagos State Safety Commission in collaboration with Buggie Consult Limited. Mojola, who was represented at the event by the Director, Legal Department of the agency, Aderonke Adekoje, maintained that the agency will continue to engage, educate and enforce safety regulations and strengthen them to ensure a zero-accident, zero-injury and zero+fatality, thus ensuring that a safer Lagos is sustained at workplace, equipment, machinery and practice in manufacturing companies throughout the state. “We will keep spreading the message of safety and ensure all employers and employees abide by all the safety standards because it is only a safer Lagos that can guarantee the attainment of a greater Lagos”, he said.Also at the event, the Director, of Training Education Skills and Development Department, Esther George, welcomed the participants and urged them to listen attentively to different facilitators who would deal with various safety rules and measures expected of individuals at their various workplaces. In his presentation, Oluwole Ojetokun dwelt extensively on the importance of personal protective equipment, as well as a selection of such equipment in workplaces and manufacturing companies. Also in his remark, the Executive Director, Buggie Consult Limited, Iginla Olalekan, commended the Lagos Safety Commission for living up to expectations as far as the safety and protection of lives and properties of Lagos residents is concerned. He implored participants to be attentive and listen to erudite instructors to be further educated on more appropriate actions to make the workplace safe and hazard-free and ensure a safer Lagos.